  "prompt": "Why do dogs pee on vehicle tyres?",
  "response": "Dogs often urinate on vehicle tires as a way of marking their territory. Urine contains scent markers that signal to other dogs the presence of the dog that left the mark. Tires, being stationary and often in areas frequented by other dogs, provide an ideal spot for this behavior.\n\nAdditionally, the scent of other animals, including the smells from the road and surrounding environment, can attract dogs to the tires, encouraging them to investigate and mark their own scent. This behavior is rooted in instinct and serves as a means of communication with other dogs in the area.",
